  "response": "If you encounter a tiger, here are some important safety tips:\n\n1. Stay calm and do not run\n- Running may trigger the tiger's predatory instincts\n- Sudden movements can provoke an attack\n\n2. Appear large and intimidating\n- Stand tall\n- Raise your arms\n- Open your jacket or shirt wide\n- Make loud noises\n- Maintain direct eye contact\n\n3. Back away slowly\n- Move away gradually without turning your back\n- Do not crouch or bend down\n- Keep facing the tiger\n\n4. If attacked, fight back\n- Target sensitive areas like eyes and nose\n- Use any available objects as weapons\n- Do not play dead\n\n5. Prevention tips\n- Avoid tiger habitats if possible\n- Travel in groups\n- Make noise when moving through tiger territory\n- Be aware of your surroundings\n\n6. Special context considerations\n- In different regions (India, Nepal, etc.), specific defensive techniques might vary\n- Local wildlife experts can provide region-specific advice\n\nRemember: Each situation is unique, and your primary goal is to avoid confrontation and escape safely.",
